Five people were left injured on Tuesday morning, two of them seriously, after a bakkie overturned on the Paradise Valley Road in Pinetown.
ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said paramedics had arrived on the scene at 7.28am to find the vehicle lying on its side in the left-hand lane of the road.Â 
"Five people were found lying on the side of the road. Paramedics assessed the patients and found that two men had sustained serious injuries while three other men had sustained minor to moderate injuries."
